resources.description: Find Customers in the Finance System, using the provided CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for Customers last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all Customers are returned.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: filter
parameters.description: The search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for accounts last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all customers are returned

parameters.name: orderBy
parameters.description: add a specific field to order by, defaults to ASC, add "!" before the field name to denote DESC

resources.description: Update a Customer given a set of partial attributes associated with a given ID in the Finance system. The update API uses the PATCH HTTP verb, so only those fields provided in the Customer object will be updated, and those fields not provided will be left alone.  Updating an Customer with a specified ID that does not exist will result in an error response.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: The customer object, with those fields that are to be updated.

resources.description: Create a Customer in the Finance system.  Customer creation will flow through Cloud Elements to the Finance Service.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description:
The Customer object to be created.
With the exception of the 'id' field, the required fields indicated in the 'Customer' model are those required to create a new customer

resources.description: Delete a customer associated with a given ID from the Finance system. This marks the customer as inactive.  Specifying a Customer associated with a given ID that does not exist will result in an error message.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the customer to delete in the Finance system.

resources.description: Find Vendors in the Finance System, using the provided CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for Vendors last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all Vendors are returned.

parameters.name: filter
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for accounts last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all vendors are returned

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied
